# Implementation Plan - Fix iOS Build & Dart Compilation

The goal is to resolve the iOS build crashing due to missing build number and the Dart compilation error regarding `authenticatedClient`.

## User Review Required
> [!IMPORTANT]
> I will be Modifying [pubspec.yaml](file:///Users/aniruddhmodi/Documents/Aniruddh/Extracurricular/flutter-app/the_30sec_journal/pubspec.yaml) to include a build number (e.g., `1.0.0+1`) to fix the Xcode "empty build number" error.

## Proposed Changes

### Configuration
#### [MODIFY] [pubspec.yaml](file:///Users/aniruddhmodi/Documents/Aniruddh/Extracurricular/flutter-app/the_30sec_journal/pubspec.yaml)
- Update `version: 1.0.0` to `version: 1.0.0+1` to ensure `$(FLUTTER_BUILD_NUMBER)` is valid.

### Code
#### [MODIFY] [drive_service.dart](file:///Users/aniruddhmodi/Documents/Aniruddh/Extracurricular/flutter-app/the_30sec_journal/lib/services/drive_service.dart)
- The method `authenticatedClient()` seems undefined for `GoogleSignInAccount` in the current context.
